                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Germantown Feb. 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1888.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Dear Sir and Friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>We were not a bit<lb/> surprised when Mr. Fleischman<lb/> told us that you had sent<lb/> us such a beautiful cake<lb/> for we knew that it was<lb/> very seldom&#44; if ever&#44; that<lb/> your name was not among<lb/> those of our benefactors.<lb/>  We all join in sending you<lb/> our heartiest and best<lb/> wishes for a merry Curim<lb/> and hope that God will<lb/> spare you with us for<lb/> many years to come.  May<lb/> He grant you a life of<lb/> peace and prosperity so<lb/> that in you we may<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>always find a true<lb/> and faithful friend<lb/> The Children of the Home<lb/> per<lb/> David Ellis.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais.<lb/>
                Dear Friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>Will you also<lb/> please accept my thanks and<lb/> those of my dear wife for your<lb/> kind attention to us and our children<lb/> Rest assured that your kind words<lb/> and kindly interested in our welfare<lb/> are a great encouragement as well<lb/> as a source of comfort to us in<lb/> our sacred task.  With best wishes<lb/> Yours very truly<lb/> <hi rend="underline">S. M. Fleischman</hi><lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>JEWISH FOSTER HOME<lb/>
                AND<lb/>
                ORPHAN ASYLUM.<lb/>
                Mill Street&#44; near Chew Germantown.<lb/>
                S. M. FLEISCHMAN&#44; SUP&#39;T.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                &#35;546 N. Fifth St.<lb/>
                City.<lb/></p>
            </body>
